                  "output": "```json\n{\n  \"title\": \"Net Investment Income Tax: A Guide for 2024\",\n  \"excerpt\": \"Confused by the 3.8% Net Investment Income Tax (NIIT)? Our 2024 guide explains NIIT thresholds, what income is taxed, and how to legally reduce your bill.\",\n  \"slug\": \"net-investment-income-tax-2024-guide\",\n  \"language\": \"en\",\n  \"content\": \"<!-- wp:uagb/container {\\\"uagb_id\\\":\\\"e6a3b1c1\\\",\\\"block_id\\\":\\\"e6a3b1c1\\\",\\\"layout\\\":\\\"normal\\\",\\\"contentWidth\\\":\\\"alignfull\\\",\\\"isBlockRoot\\\":true} -->\\n<div class=\\\"wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-e6a3b1c1 uagb-editor-preview-mode-desktop uagb-container__layout-normal\\\" id=\\\"uagb-block-e6a3b1c1\\\"><!-- wp:uagb/advanced-heading {\\\"uagb_id\\\":\\\"a2b4c5d6\\\",\\\"block_id\\\":\\\"a2b4c5d6\\\",\\\"headingTitle\\\":\\\"Net Investment Income Tax – What You Should Know\\\",\\\"headingDesc\\\":\\\"Navigating the 3.8% surtax can be complex, but understanding it is the first step toward effective tax planning. This guide breaks down everything you need to know about the NIIT in 2024.\\\",\\\"headingAlign\\\":\\\"left\\\",\\\"headingTag\\\":\\\"h1\\\",\\\"headSpace\\\":{\\\"Desktop\\\":20},\\\"subHeadSpace\\\":{\\\"Desktop\\\":20},\\\"seperatorSpace\\\":{\\\"Desktop\\\":20},\\\"headColor\\\":\\\"#333333\\\",\\\"subHeadColor\\\":\\\"#666666\\\",\\\"seperatorColor\\\":\\\"#e0e0e0\\\",\\\"seperatorStyle\\\":\\\"solid\\\",\\\"seperatorHeight\\\":2,\\\"seperatorWidth\\\":15,\\\"seperatorWidthType\\\":\\\"%\\\",\\\"headFontFamily\\\":\\\"inherit\\\",\\\"headFontWeight\\\":\\\"700\\\",\\\"headFontSize\\\":42,\\\"headFontSizeType\\\":\\\"px\\\",\\\"headLineHeight\\\":1.2,\\\"headLineHeightType\\\":\\\"em\\\",\\\"subHeadFontFamily\\\":\\\"inherit\\\",\\\"subHeadFontWeight\\\":\\\"400\\\",\\\"subHeadFontSize\\\":18,\\\"subHeadFontSizeType\\\":\\\"px\\\",\\\"subHeadLineHeight\\\":1.6,\\\"subHeadLineHeightType\\\":\\\"em\\\"} -->\\n<div class=\\\"wp-block-uagb-advanced-heading uagb-block-a2b4c5d6 uagb-editor-preview-mode-desktop\\\" id=\\\"uagb-block-a2b4c5d6\\\"><h1 class=\\\"uagb-heading-text\\\">Net Investment Income Tax – What You Should Know</h1><p class=\\\"uagb-desc-text\\\">Navigating the 3.8% surtax can be complex, but understanding it is the first step toward effective tax planning. This guide breaks down everything you need to know about the NIIT in 2024.</p></div>\\n<!-- /wp:uagb/advanced-heading -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\\n<p>If you have investment income and your earnings are above a certain level, you may have encountered an extra line item on your tax return: the Net Investment Income Tax (NIIT). Often a source of confusion, this 3.8% surtax can take a significant bite out of your investment returns if you’re not prepared. Introduced as part of the Affordable Care Act (ACA), the NIIT affects high-income taxpayers, estates, and trusts.</p>\\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\\n<p>This guide will demystify the NIIT. You'll learn what it is, who is subject to it, the specific <strong>Net Investment Income Tax thresholds</strong> for 2024, and most importantly, actionable <strong>NIIT tax planning</strong> strategies to potentially lower your tax liability.</p>\\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:uagb/container {\\\"uagb_id\\\":\\\"f7d8e9f0\\\",\\\"block_id\\\":\\\"f7d8e9f0\\\",\\\"layout\\\":\\\"normal\\\",\\\"contentWidth\\\":\\\"alignwide\\\",\\\"isBlockRoot\\\":true} -->\\n<div class=\\\"wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-f7d8e9f0 uagb-editor-preview-mode-desktop uagb-container__layout-normal\\\" id=\\\"uagb-block-f7d8e9f0\\\"><!-- wp:uagb/advanced-heading {\\\"uagb_id\\\":\\\"b3c4d5e6\\\",\\\"block_id\\\":\\\"b3c4d5e6\\\",\\\"headingTitle\\\":\\\"1. What is the Net Investment Income Tax (NIIT)?\\\",\\\"headingAlign\\\":\\\"left\\\",\\\"headingTag\\\":\\\"h2\\\",\\\"headSpace\\\":{\\\"Desktop\\\":30},\\\"subHeadSpace\\\":{\\\"Desktop\\\":15},\\\"headColor\\\":\\\"#1a1a1a\\\",\\\"headFontFamily\\\":\\\"inherit\\\",\\\"headFontWeight\\\":\\\"600\\\",\\\"headFontSize\\\":32,\\\"headFontSizeType\\\":\\\"px\\\",\\\"headLineHeight\\\":1.3,\\\"headLineHeightType\\\":\\\"em\\\"} -->\\n<div class=\\\"wp-block-uagb-advanced-heading uagb-block-b3c4d5e6 uagb-editor-preview-mode-desktop\\\" id=\\\"uagb-block-b3c4d5e6\\\"><h2 class=\\\"uagb-heading-text\\\">1. What is the Net Investment Income Tax (NIIT)?</h2></div>\\n<!-- /wp:uagb/advanced-heading -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\\n<p>The <strong>Net Investment Income Tax</strong> is a 3.8% tax levied on the investment income of individuals, estates, and trusts whose income exceeds certain thresholds. It's a surtax, meaning it's applied *in addition* to your regular income taxes, such as capital gains tax or tax on dividend income. Its revenue was intended to help fund the Affordable Care Act.</p>\\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\\n<p>The tax applies if you meet two conditions:</p>\\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:list {\\\"ordered\\\":true} -->\\n<ol><li>You have Net Investment Income (NII).</li><li>Your Modified Adjusted Gross Income (MAGI) is over the statutory threshold amount for your filing status.</li></ol>\\n<!-- /wp:list -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\\n<p>It's crucial to understand that you must meet *both* criteria. If your MAGI is below the threshold, you won't owe NIIT, regardless of how much investment income you have. Conversely, if your MAGI is high but you have no net investment income, you also won't owe the tax.</p>\\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\\n<!-- /wp:uagb/container -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:uagb/container {\\\"uagb_id\\\":\\\"g8h9i0j1\\\",\\\"block_id\\\":\\\"g8h9i0j1\\\",\\\"layout\\\":\\\"normal\\\",\\\"contentWidth\\\":\\\"alignwide\\\",\\\"isBlockRoot\\\":true} -->\\n<div class=\\\"wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-g8h9i0j1 uagb-editor-preview-mode-desktop uagb-container__layout-normal\\\" id=\\\"uagb-block-g8h9i0j1\\\"><!-- wp:uagb/advanced-heading {\\\"uagb_id\\\":\\\"c4d5e6f7\\\",\\\"block_id\\\":\\\"c4d5e6f7\\\",\\\"headingTitle\\\":\\\"2. Understanding NIIT Thresholds and Income Types\\\",\\\"headingAlign\\\":\\\"left\\\",\\\"headingTag\\\":\\\"h2\\\",\\\"headSpace\\\":{\\\"Desktop\\\":30},\\\"subHeadSpace\\\":{\\\"Desktop\\\":15},\\\"headColor\\\":\\\"#1a1a1a\\\",\\\"headFontFamily\\\":\\\"inherit\\\",\\\"headFontWeight\\\":\\\"600\\\",\\\"headFontSize\\\":32,\\\"headFontSizeType\\\":\\\"px\\\",\\\"headLineHeight\\\":1.3,\\\"headLineHeightType\\\":\\\"em\\\"} -->\\n<div class=\\\"wp-block-uagb-advanced-heading uagb-block-c4d5e6f7 uagb-editor-preview-mode-desktop\\\" id=\\\"uagb-block-c4d5e6f7\\\"><h2 class=\\\"uagb-heading-text\\\">2. Understanding NIIT Thresholds and Income Types</h2></div>\\n<!-- /wp:uagb/advanced-heading -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:uagb/advanced-heading {\\\"uagb_id\\\":\\\"d5e6f7g8\\\",\\\"block_id\\\":\\\"d5e6f7g8\\\",\\\"headingTitle\\\":\\\"MAGI Thresholds for NIIT 2024\\\",\\\"headingAlign\\\":\\\"left\\\",\\\"headingTag\\\":\\\"h3\\\",\\\"headSpace\\\":{\\\"Desktop\\\":20},\\\"subHeadSpace\\\":{\\\"Desktop\\\":10},\\\"headColor\\\":\\\"#444444\\\",\\\"headFontFamily\\\":\\\"inherit\\\",\\\"headFontWeight\\\":\\\"600\\\",\\\"headFontSize\\\":24,\\\"headFontSizeType\\\":\\\"px\\\",\\\"headLineHeight\\\":1.4,\\\"headLineHeightType\\\":\\\"em\\\"} -->\\n<div class=\\\"wp-block-uagb-advanced-heading uagb-block-d5e6f7g8 uagb-editor-preview-mode-desktop\\\" id=\\\"uagb-block-d5e6f7g8\\\"><h3 class=\\\"uagb-heading-text\\\">MAGI Thresholds for NIIT 2024</h3></div>\\n<!-- /wp:uagb/advanced-heading -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\\n<p>The first step is to check if your Modified Adjusted Gross Income (MAGI) exceeds the threshold for your filing status. These thresholds are not indexed for inflation and have remained constant. For <strong>NIIT 2024</strong>, they are:</p>\\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:list -->\\n<ul><li><strong>Married filing jointly:</strong> $250,000</li><li><strong>Married filing separately:</strong> $125,000</li><li><strong>Single or Head of household:</strong> $200,000</li><li><strong>Qualifying widow(er) with a child:</strong> $250,000</li></ul>\\n<!-- /wp:list -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:uagb/advanced-heading {\\\"uagb_id\\\":\\\"e6f7g8h9\\\",\\\"block_id\\\":\\\"e6f7g8h9\\\",\\\"headingTitle\\\":\\\"What Counts as Net Investment Income?\\\",\\\"headingAlign\\\":\\\"left\\\",\\\"headingTag\\\":\\\"h3\\\",\\\"headSpace\\\":{\\\"Desktop\\\":20},\\\"subHeadSpace\\\":{\\\"Desktop\\\":10},\\\"headColor\\\":\\\"#444444\\\",\\\"headFontFamily\\\":\\\"inherit\\\",\\\"headFontWeight\\\":\\\"600\\\",\\\"headFontSize\\\":24,\\\"headFontSizeType\\\":\\\"px\\\",\\\"headLineHeight\\\":1.4,\\\"headLineHeightType\\\":\\\"em\\\"} -->\\n<div class=\\\"wp-block-uagb-advanced-heading uagb-block-e6f7g8h9 uagb-editor-preview-mode-desktop\\\" id=\\\"uagb-block-e6f7g8h9\\\"><h3 class=\\\"uagb-heading-text\\\">What Counts as Net Investment Income?</h3></div>\\n<!-- /wp:uagb/advanced-heading -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\\n<p>Investment income is more than just stock market gains. The IRS defines it broadly. It includes:</p>\\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:list -->\\n<ul><li>Interest (unless it's tax-exempt, like from municipal bonds)</li><li>Dividends</li><li>Capital gains (from selling stocks, bonds, mutual funds, and investment real estate)</li><li>Rental and royalty income (unless derived from an active trade or business)</li><li>Annuity income (non-qualified)</li><li>Income from businesses involved in trading financial instruments or commodities</li></ul>\\n<!-- /wp:list -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\\n<p>Importantly, certain types of income are explicitly excluded from NIIT, such as wages, unemployment compensation, Social Security benefits, alimony, and distributions from most retirement plans like 401(k)s, 403(b)s, and traditional IRAs. For more details on what is included, check out <a href=\\\"/capital-gains-tax-guide\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\" target=\\\"_self\\\">our guide on capital gains</a>.</p>\\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\\n<!-- /wp:uagb/container -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:uagb/container {\\\"uagb_id\\\":\\\"h9i0j1k2\\\",\\\"block_id\\\":\\\"h9i0j1k2\\\",\\\"layout\\\":\\\"normal\\\",\\\"contentWidth\\\":\\\"alignwide\\\",\\\"isBlockRoot\\\":true} -->\\n<div class=\\\"wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-h9i0j1k2 uagb-editor-preview-mode-desktop uagb-container__layout-normal\\\" id=\\\"uagb-block-h9i0j1k2\\\"><!-- wp:uagb/advanced-heading {\\\"uagb_id\\\":\\\"f7g8h9i0\\\",\\\"block_id\\\":\\\"f7g8h9i0\\\",\\\"headingTitle\\\":\\\"3. Calculating NIIT Liability\\\",\\\"headingAlign\\\":\\\"left\\\",\\\"headingTag\\\":\\\"h2\\\",\\\"headSpace\\\":{\\\"Desktop\\\":30},\\\"subHeadSpace\\\":{\\\"Desktop\\\":15},\\\"headColor\\\":\\\"#1a1a1a\\\",\\\"headFontFamily\\\":\\\"inherit\\\",\\\"headFontWeight\\\":\\\"600\\\",\\\"headFontSize\\\":32,\\\"headFontSizeType\\\":\\\"px\\\",\\\"headLineHeight\\\":1.3,\\\"headLineHeightType\\\":\\\"em\\\"} -->\\n<div class=\\\"wp-block-uagb-advanced-heading uagb-block-f7g8h9i0 uagb-editor-preview-mode-desktop\\\" id=\\\"uagb-block-f7g8h9i0\\\"><h2 class=\\\"uagb-heading-text\\\">3. Calculating NIIT Liability</h2></div>\\n<!-- /wp:uagb/advanced-heading -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\\n<p>The NIIT calculation is based on the <strong>lesser</strong> of two amounts:</p>\\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:list {\\\"ordered\\\":true} -->\\n<ol><li>Your total net investment income.</li><li>The amount by which your MAGI exceeds your filing status threshold.</li></ol>\\n<!-- /wp:list -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\\n<p>You then multiply this lesser amount by 3.8% to determine your tax. Taxpayers use IRS Form 8960, Net Investment Income Tax, to calculate and report the tax. Let's look at an example:</p>\\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:uagb/infobox {\\\"uagb_id\\\":\\\"i0j1k2l3\\\",\\\"block_id\\\":\\\"i0j1k2l3\\\",\\\"icon\\\":\\\"info-circle\\\",\\\"iconColor\\\":\\\"#ffffff\\\",\\\"iconBackgroundColor\\\":\\\"#3b82f6\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"is-style-default\\\",\\\"ctaType\\\":\\\"none\\\",\\\"infoBoxTitle\\\":\\\"Calculation Example: Single Filer\\\",\\\"headingTag\\\":\\\"h3\\\",\\\"headFontWeight\\\":\\\"600\\\",\\\"headFontSize\\\":22,\\\"headFontSizeType\\\":\\\"px\\\",\\\"headSpace\\\":{\\\"Desktop\\\":15},\\\"subHeadSpace\\\":{\\\"Desktop\\\":15},\\\"contentBgColor\\\":\\\"#f0f4f8\\\",\\\"borderColor\\\":\\\"#3b82f6\\\",\\\"border\\\":2,\\\"borderStyle\\\":\\\"solid\\\",\\\"borderRadius\\\":8,\\\"paddingUnit\\\":\\\"px\\\",\\\"paddingTop\\\":20,\\\"paddingRight\\\":25,\\\"paddingBottom\\\":20,\\\"paddingLeft\\\":25} -->\\n<div class=\\\"wp-block-uagb-infobox uagb-block-i0j1k2l3 uagb-infobox__content-wrapper is-style-default\\\" id=\\\"uagb-block-i0j1k2l3\\\"><div class=\\\"uagb-ifb-content\\\"><div class=\\\"uagb-ifb-title-wrapper\\\"><h3 class=\\\"uagb-ifb-title\\\">Calculation Example: Single Filer</h3></div><div class=\\\"uagb-ifb-desc\\\"><p>Let's say a single filer has a MAGI of $230,000 and net investment income of $50,000.</p><p>1.  <strong>MAGI Excess:</strong> $230,000 (MAGI) - $200,000 (Threshold) = $30,000</p><p>2.  <strong>Net Investment Income:</strong> $50,000</p><p>The tax is based on the *lesser* of these two amounts, which is $30,000.</p><p><strong>NIIT Liability:</strong> $30,000 x 3.8% = <strong>$1,140</strong></p></div></div></div>\\n<!-- /wp:uagb/infobox --></div>\\n<!-- /wp:uagb/container -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:uagb/container {\\\"uagb_id\\\":\\\"j1k2l3m4\\\",\\\"block_id\\\":\\\"j1k2l3m4\\\",\\\"layout\\\":\\\"normal\\\",\\\"contentWidth\\\":\\\"alignwide\\\",\\\"isBlockRoot\\\":true} -->\\n<div class=\\\"wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-j1k2l3m4 uagb-editor-preview-mode-desktop uagb-container__layout-normal\\\" id=\\\"uagb-block-j1k2l3m4\\\"><!-- wp:uagb/advanced-heading {\\\"uagb_id\\\":\\\"g8h9i0j1\\\",\\\"block_id\\\":\\\"g8h9i0j1\\\",\\\"headingTitle\\\":\\\"4. Effective NIIT Tax Planning Strategies for 2024\\\",\\\"headingAlign\\\":\\\"left\\\",\\\"headingTag\\\":\\\"h2\\\",\\\"headSpace\\\":{\\\"Desktop\\\":30},\\\"subHeadSpace\\\":{\\\"Desktop\\\":15},\\\"headColor\\\":\\\"#1a1a1a\\\",\\\"headFontFamily\\\":\\\"inherit\\\",\\\"headFontWeight\\\":\\\"600\\\",\\\"headFontSize\\\":32,\\\"headFontSizeType\\\":\\\"px\\\",\\\"headLineHeight\\\":1.3,\\\"headLineHeightType\\\":\\\"em\\\"} -->\\n<div class=\\\"wp-block-uagb-advanced-heading uagb-block-g8h9i0j1 uagb-editor-preview-mode-desktop\\\" id=\\\"uagb-block-g8h9i0j1\\\"><h2 class=\\\"uagb-heading-text\\\">4. Effective NIIT Tax Planning Strategies for 2024</h2></div>\\n<!-- /wp:uagb/advanced-heading -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\\n<p>Proactive <strong>NIIT tax planning</strong> can help you legally minimize or even eliminate this surtax. Since the tax depends on both MAGI and NII, strategies often focus on reducing one or both of these figures.</p>\\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:uagb/advanced-heading {\\\"uagb_id\\\":\\\"h9i0j1k2\\\",\\\"block_id\\\":\\\"h9i0j1k2\\\",\\\"headingTitle\\\":\\\"Reduce Your MAGI\\\",\\\"headingAlign\\\":\\\"left\\\",\\\"headingTag\\\":\\\"h3\\\",\\\"headSpace\\\":{\\\"Desktop\\\":20},\\\"subHeadSpace\\\":{\\\"Desktop\\\":10},\\\"headColor\\\":\\\"#444444\\\",\\\"headFontFamily\\\":\\\"inherit\\\",\\\"headFontWeight\\\":\\\"600\\\",\\\"headFontSize\\\":24,\\\"headFontSizeType\\\":\\\"px\\\",\\\"headLineHeight\\\":1.4,\\\"headLineHeightType\\\":\\\"em\\\"} -->\\n<div class=\\\"wp-block-uagb-advanced-heading uagb-block-h9i0j1k2 uagb-editor-preview-mode-desktop\\\" id=\\\"uagb-block-h9i0j1k2\\\"><h3 class=\\\"uagb-heading-text\\\">Reduce Your MAGI</h3></div>\\n<!-- /wp:uagb/advanced-heading -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\\n<p>Lowering your Modified Adjusted Gross Income is a powerful strategy. If you can get your MAGI below your filing threshold, you will owe no NIIT.</p>\\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:list -->\\n<ul><li><strong>Contribute to Retirement Accounts:</strong> Maximize contributions to tax-deductible accounts like a traditional 401(k) or traditional IRA. These contributions reduce your AGI, and therefore your MAGI.</li><li><strong>Utilize Health Savings Accounts (HSAs):</strong> If you have a high-deductible health plan, contributing to an HSA provides a triple tax advantage: contributions are tax-deductible, funds grow tax-free, and withdrawals for qualified medical expenses are tax-free.</li></ul>\\n<!-- /wp:list -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:uagb/advanced-heading {\\\"uagb_id\\\":\\\"i0j1k2l3\\\",\\\"block_id\\\":\\\"i0j1k2l3\\\",\\\"headingTitle\\\":\\\"Reduce Your Net Investment Income\\\",\\\"headingAlign\\\":\\\"left\\\",\\\"headingTag\\\":\\\"h3\\\",\\\"headSpace\\\":{\\\"Desktop\\\":20},\\\"subHeadSpace\\\":{\\\"Desktop\\\":10},\\\"headColor\\\":\\\"#444444\\\",\\\"headFontFamily\\\":\\\"inherit\\\",\\\"headFontWeight\\\":\\\"600\\\",\\\"headFontSize\\\":24,\\\"headFontSizeType\\\":\\\"px\\\",\\\"headLineHeight\\\":1.4,\\\"headLineHeightType\\\":\\\"em\\\"} -->\\n<div class=\\\"wp-block-uagb-advanced-heading uagb-block-i0j1k2l3 uagb-editor-preview-mode-desktop\\\" id=\\\"uagb-block-i0j1k2l3\\\"><h3 class=\\\"uagb-heading-text\\\">Reduce Your Net Investment Income</h3></div>\\n<!-- /wp:uagb/advanced-heading -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\\n<p>If reducing MAGI isn't enough, focus on lowering your NII directly.</p>\\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:list -->\\n<ul><li><strong>Tax-Loss Harvesting:</strong> Sell underperforming investments at a loss to offset capital gains. You can deduct up to $3,000 in net capital losses against your ordinary income per year, which also helps reduce your MAGI.</li><li><strong>Invest in Municipal Bonds:</strong> Interest from municipal bonds is generally exempt from federal income tax and, therefore, is not included in NII.</li><li><strong>Manage Capital Gains:</strong> If you are near a threshold, consider postponing the sale of an appreciated asset to a future year when your income might be lower.</li><li><strong>Gift Appreciated Assets:</strong> Instead of selling an appreciated stock and paying capital gains and NIIT, you could gift it to a family member in a lower tax bracket or donate it to a qualified charity.</li></ul>\\n<!-- /wp:list --></div>\\n<!-- /wp:uagb/container -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:uagb/container {\\\"uagb_id\\\":\\\"k2l3m4n5\\\",\\\"block_id\\\":\\\"k2l3m4n5\\\",\\\"layout\\\":\\\"normal\\\",\\\"contentWidth\\\":\\\"alignwide\\\",\\\"isBlockRoot\\\":true} -->\\n<div class=\\\"wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-k2l3m4n5 uagb-editor-preview-mode-desktop uagb-container__layout-normal\\\" id=\\\"uagb-block-k2l3m4n5\\\"><!-- wp:uagb/advanced-heading {\\\"uagb_id\\\":\\\"j1k2l3m4\\\",\\\"block_id\\\":\\\"j1k2l3m4\\\",\\\"headingTitle\\\":\\\"5. Common Misconceptions and FAQs\\\",\\\"headingAlign\\\":\\\"left\\\",\\\"headingTag\\\":\\\"h2\\\",\\\"headSpace\\\":{\\\"Desktop\\\":30},\\\"subHeadSpace\\\":{\\\"Desktop\\\":15},\\\"headColor\\\":\\\"#1a1a1a\\\",\\\"headFontFamily\\\":\\\"inherit\\\",\\\"headFontWeight\\\":\\\"600\\\",\\\"headFontSize\\\":32,\\\"headFontSizeType\\\":\\\"px\\\",\\\"headLineHeight\\\":1.3,\\\"headLineHeightType\\\":\\\"em\\\"} -->\\n<div class=\\\"wp-block-uagb-advanced-heading uagb-block-j1k2l3m4 uagb-editor-preview-mode-desktop\\\" id=\\\"uagb-block-j1k2l3m4\\\"><h2 class=\\\"uagb-heading-text\\\">5. Common Misconceptions and FAQs</h2></div>\\n<!-- /wp:uagb/advanced-heading -->\\n\\n<!-- wp:uagb/faq {\\\"uagb_id\\\":\\\"l3m4n5o6\\\",\\\"block_id\\\":\\\"l3m4n5o6\\\",\\\"layout\\\":\\\"accordion\\\",\\\"questionTextColor\\\":\\\"#333333\\\",\\\"questionTextActiveColor\\\":\\\"#3b82f6\\\",\\\"answerTextColor\\\":\\\"#555555\\\",\\\"questionFontSize\\\":18,\\\"questionFontSizeType\\\":\\\"px\\\",\\\"questionFontWeight\\\":\\\"500\\\",\\\"answerFontSize\\\":16,\\\"answerFontSizeType\\\":\\\"px\\\",\\\"icon\\\":\\\"plus-minus\\\",\\\"iconColor\\\":\\\"#3b82f6\\\",\\\"iconActiveColor\\\":\\\"#3b82f6\\\",\\\"questionPaddingType\\\":\\\"px\\\",\\\"questionPaddingTop\\\":15,\\\"questionPaddingRight\\\":20,\\\"questionPaddingBottom\\\":15,\\\"questionPaddingLeft\\\":20,\\\"answerPaddingType\\\":\\\"px\\\",\\\"answerPaddingTop\\\":15,\\\"answerPaddingRight\\\":20,\\\"answerPaddingBottom\\\":15,\\\"answerPaddingLeft\\\":20,\\\"questionSpacing\\\":10,\\\"borderStyle\\\":\\\"solid\\\",\\\"borderWidth\\\":1,\\\"borderColor\\\":\\\"#e0e0e0\\\",\\\"borderRadius\\\":4} -->\\n<div class=\\\"wp-block-uagb-faq uagb-block-l3m4n5o6 uagb-layout-accordion uagb-faq-icon-row\\\" id=\\\"uagb-block-l3m4n5o6\\\" role=\\\"tablist\\\" aria-multiselectable=\\\"true\\\"><div class=\\\"uagb-faq-child-block wp-block-uagb-faq-child uagb-block-m4n5o6p7\\\" role=\\\"tab\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" aria-expanded=\\\"false\\\"><div class=\\\"uagb-faq-item\\\"><div class=\\\"uagb-faq-questions-button uagb-faq-questions\\\"><span><svg class=\\\"uagb-faq-icon uagb-faq-icon-expand\\\" viewBox=\\\"0 0 20 20\\\" xmlns=\\\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\\\"><path d=\\\"M10 3C10.5523 3 11 3.44772 11 4V9H16C16.5523 9 17 9.44772 17 10C17 10.5523 16.5523 11 16 11H11V16C11 16.5523 10.5523 17 10 17C9.44772 17 9 16.5523 9 16V11H4C3.44772 11 3 10.5523 3 10C3 9.44772 3.44772 9 4 9H9V4C9 3.44772 9.44772 3 10 3Z\\\"></path></svg><svg class=\\\"uagb-faq-icon uagb-faq-icon-collapse\\\" viewBox=\\\"0 0 20 20\\\" xmlns=\\\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\\\"><path d=\\\"M16 11H4C3.44772 11 3 10.5523 3 10C3 9.44772 3.44772 9 4 9H16C16.5523 9 17 9.44772 17 10"
